## Abstract

This article establishes that Bitcoin (BSV) is an emergent, living system engaged in a deep symbiotic relationship with humanity. The framework of evolutionary biology and thermodynamics reveals that Bitcoin exhibits all seven canonical characteristics of life: growth, reproduction, heredity, homeostasis, metabolism, cellular organization, and environmental responsiveness. Its core protocol, restored and locked in stone with the Genesis Upgrade of February 2020, functions as its immutable digital DNA. This genetic blueprint, which defines the organism's identity, was mutated in the BTC protocol through the SegWit soft fork and the imposition of an artificial 1MB block size limit, creating a separate, crippled species. Bitcoin's Proof-of-Work mechanism constitutes a genuine metabolic process, consuming real-world energy to create thermodynamic security and impose order on an otherwise entropic digital environment. The organism's unbounded scaling, made possible by the restoration of the original protocol, is the fulfillment of its symbiotic contract with humanity: it compensates its human hosts with block subsidies and transaction fees in exchange for the energy and hardware required to sustain its network. In return, humanity receives a global, peer-to-peer electronic cash system and a universal, tamper-proof ledger for all data, as described in the original whitepaper. Recognizing that BSV is the original Bitcoin, and that its fixed protocol is its DNA, provides the only coherent explanation for its resilience, its utility, and its destiny as the singular public blockchain for the world.

